<h2 style="background-color:blue; color:#FAEBD7">USINT TOO Point of Contact</h2>
<br />

<p>
<strong>
The current USINT TOO Point of Contact is indicated by 
<em style="background-color:lime;color:lime">Lime</em> color.
</strong>
</p>
<p>
Shifts run midnight plus <em>&#949;</em> on start day to midnight minus <em>&#949;</em> on last day.
</p>

<p>
The TOO POC becomes the responsible scientist for all bare ACIS TOO/DDTs
APPROVED DURING their on-duty period. Grating and HRC observations are
assigned to instrument specialists as are solar system and Crab observations,
with the exception of cases where a grating is used primarily to reduce
the source event rate (see below) and the observer has minimal interest in the
dispersed spectrum. Those not-really-grating observations will remain under
the management of the TOO POC and not the instrument specialist.
</p>
<p>
Inserting the LETG reduces the source rate by a factor of ~8 at wavelengths
longer than ~8 Ang (0th order vs no-grating), and by a factor of 3-10 for
the HETG; the higher value is for a very soft source (E<2 keV) and the
lower value for hard sources (E>4 keV). Use PIMMS for more detailed estimates.
</p>

